issue_body:
At the moment you have to explicitly name the cassette file in the path parameter when using decorator:

    @vcr.use_cassette('article_header.yaml')
    def test_get_article_header_text_from_url():
        # rest of function...
    # cassette is saved as 'article_header.yaml'

Is it possible to dynamically generate cassette's name so it's taken from the decorated function instead?

    @vcr.use_cassette(func_name)
    def test_get_article_header_text_from_url():
        # rest of function...
    # cassette is saved as 'test_get_article_header_text_from_url.yaml'

It's possible to filter guild messages from specific users using the following endpoint.
```
/guilds/{}/messages/search?author_id={}&include_nsfw=true&count=25&offset={}
```

This returns JSON structured like so.
```json
{
    "messages": [
        [
            {
                // Message context. 
            },
            {
                // Message context. 
            },
            {
                // A message sent by the user we are filtering. This is always message[2].
            },
            {
                // Message context. 
            },
            {
                // Message context.
            }
        ],
        ...
    ]
}
```

I will be happy to submit a PR for this if the functionality is approved.

